<annotation id="annotation_558977" type="text" style="popup" log_data="xble=1&amp;ei=oLoeXJ6eIcy0hga7kLuACg&amp;a-v=OXt5qeqEIQI&amp;a-type=1&amp;a-id=annotation_558977" itct="CAcQs-UBGP___________wEiEwie7tCZvrTfAhVMmsEKHTvIDqAo-B0yAml2SILCkNSetd69OQ">
  <TEXT>Before heading off to Wily&#39;s Castle, I opted to collect a few more screws to get the Power Generator. This item helps out tremendously to balance the issues of certain weapons using up too much ammo.</TEXT>
  <segment>
    <movingRegion type="rect">
      <rectRegion x="0.00000" y="0.00000" w="100.00000" h="22.22200" t="0:00:00.3"/>
      <rectRegion x="0.00000" y="0.00000" w="100.00000" h="22.22200" t="0:00:06.3"/>
    </movingRegion>
  </segment>
  <appearance bgAlpha="0.600000023842" bgColor="0" fgColor="16777215" textSize="3.9116" effects="textdropshadow">
    <padding top="2.34696006775" left="2.05074167252" bottom="2.34696006775" right="2.73432230949"/>
  </appearance>
  
</annotation>
<annotation id="annotation_576230" type="text" style="popup" log_data="xble=1&amp;ei=oLoeXJ6eIcy0hga7kLuACg&amp;a-v=OXt5qeqEIQI&amp;a-type=1&amp;a-id=annotation_576230" itct="CAgQs-UBGP___________wEiEwie7tCZvrTfAhVMmsEKHTvIDqAo-B0yAml2SILCkNSetd69OQ">
  <TEXT>Also, I forgot that the Wild Sprint doesn&#39;t work in mid-air unless you jump after using it.</TEXT>
  <segment>
    <movingRegion type="rect">
      <rectRegion x="0.00000" y="0.00000" w="100.00000" h="13.33300" t="0:04:12.3"/>
      <rectRegion x="0.00000" y="0.00000" w="100.00000" h="13.33300" t="0:04:17.3"/>
    </movingRegion>
  </segment>
  <appearance bgAlpha="0.600000023842" bgColor="0" fgColor="16777215" textSize="3.9116" effects="textdropshadow">
    <padding top="2.34696006775" left="2.05074167252" bottom="2.34696006775" right="2.73432230949"/>
  </appearance>
  
</annotation>
<annotation id="annotation_646565" type="text" style="popup" log_data="xble=1&amp;ei=oLoeXJ6eIcy0hga7kLuACg&amp;a-v=OXt5qeqEIQI&amp;a-type=1&amp;a-id=annotation_646565" itct="CAkQs-UBGP___________wEiEwie7tCZvrTfAhVMmsEKHTvIDqAo-B0yAml2SILCkNSetd69OQ">
  <TEXT>Yeah, I know - but honestly, I really don&#39;t feel like taking any chances. Besides, you can always buy more in the shop, or just let the game shower you with them in later stages.</TEXT>
  <segment>
    <movingRegion type="rect">
      <rectRegion x="0.00000" y="81.66700" w="100.00000" h="18.33300" t="0:05:21.9"/>
      <rectRegion x="0.00000" y="81.66700" w="100.00000" h="18.33300" t="0:05:28.9"/>
    </movingRegion>
  </segment>
  <appearance bgAlpha="0.600000023842" bgColor="0" fgColor="16777215" textSize="3.9116" effects="textdropshadow">
    <padding top="2.34696006775" left="2.05074167252" bottom="2.34696006775" right="2.73432230949"/>
  </appearance>
  
</annotation>
<annotation id="annotation_687463" type="text" style="popup" log_data="xble=1&amp;ei=oLoeXJ6eIcy0hga7kLuACg&amp;a-v=OXt5qeqEIQI&amp;a-type=1&amp;a-id=annotation_687463" itct="CAoQs-UBGP___________wEiEwie7tCZvrTfAhVMmsEKHTvIDqAo-B0yAml2SILCkNSetd69OQ">
  <TEXT>After that, we come to yet another &#39;gimmick room.&#39; The entire room is dark, and portions of it can only be seen through that light - which also has a overly-waving pattern to it.</TEXT>
  <segment>
    <movingRegion type="rect">
      <rectRegion x="0.00000" y="0.00000" w="100.00000" h="17.77800" t="0:07:29.2"/>
      <rectRegion x="0.00000" y="0.00000" w="100.00000" h="17.77800" t="0:07:36.2"/>
    </movingRegion>
  </segment>
  <appearance bgAlpha="0.600000023842" bgColor="0" fgColor="16777215" textSize="3.9116" effects="textdropshadow">
    <padding top="2.34696006775" left="2.05074167252" bottom="2.34696006775" right="2.73432230949"/>
  </appearance>
  
</annotation>
<annotation id="annotation_700628" type="text" style="popup" log_data="xble=1&amp;ei=oLoeXJ6eIcy0hga7kLuACg&amp;a-v=OXt5qeqEIQI&amp;a-type=1&amp;a-id=annotation_700628" itct="">
  <TEXT>The first fortress boss is another &#39;gimmick battle&#39; of sorts. The idea behind it is kind of interesting, but I absolutely suck at trying to lure this thing into the right spot. Most of the time, as you&#39;ll see here, it actually goes sailing in the exact opposite direction of where I need it to be.</TEXT>
  <segment>
    <movingRegion type="rect">
      <rectRegion x="0.00000" y="0.00000" w="100.00000" h="26.66700" t="0:04:22.5"/>
      <rectRegion x="0.00000" y="0.00000" w="100.00000" h="26.66700" t="0:04:33.5"/>
    </movingRegion>
  </segment>
  <appearance bgAlpha="0.600000023842" bgColor="0" fgColor="16777215" textSize="3.9116" effects="textdropshadow">
    <padding top="2.34696006775" left="2.05074167252" bottom="2.34696006775" right="2.73432230949"/>
  </appearance>
  
</annotation>
<annotation id="annotation_709435" type="text" style="popup" log_data="xble=1&amp;ei=oLoeXJ6eIcy0hga7kLuACg&amp;a-v=OXt5qeqEIQI&amp;a-type=1&amp;a-id=annotation_709435" itct="">
  <TEXT>The Yellow Devil can be a difficult to deal with, even though there&#39;s actually a spot marked on the floor to help you avoid some of his moves. Like with the rest of this level, however, there&#39;s a method you can use to beat him rather easily.</TEXT>
  <segment>
    <movingRegion type="rect">
      <rectRegion x="0.00000" y="0.00000" w="100.00000" h="22.22200" t="0:11:16.5"/>
      <rectRegion x="0.00000" y="0.00000" w="100.00000" h="22.22200" t="0:11:25.5"/>
    </movingRegion>
  </segment>
  <appearance bgAlpha="0.600000023842" bgColor="0" fgColor="16777215" textSize="3.9116" effects="textdropshadow">
    <padding top="2.34696006775" left="2.05074167252" bottom="2.34696006775" right="2.73432230949"/>
  </appearance>
  
</annotation>
<annotation id="annotation_774136" type="text" style="popup" log_data="xble=1&amp;ei=oLoeXJ6eIcy0hga7kLuACg&amp;a-v=OXt5qeqEIQI&amp;a-type=1&amp;a-id=annotation_774136" itct="">
  <TEXT>This section can be a bit troublesome. As far as I know, the enemy at the top can&#39;t be killed, and the spikes he drops are insta-kills as well. Fortunately, you can outright avoid any damage here by using the Wild Sprint.</TEXT>
  <segment>
    <movingRegion type="rect">
      <rectRegion x="0.00000" y="76.66700" w="100.00000" h="23.33300" t="0:02:10.5"/>
      <rectRegion x="0.00000" y="76.66700" w="100.00000" h="23.33300" t="0:02:20.5"/>
    </movingRegion>
  </segment>
  <appearance bgAlpha="0.600000023842" bgColor="0" fgColor="16777215" textSize="3.9116" effects="textdropshadow">
    <padding top="2.34696006775" left="2.05074167252" bottom="2.34696006775" right="2.73432230949"/>
  </appearance>
  
</annotation>
<annotation id="annotation_883706" type="text" style="popup" log_data="xble=1&amp;ei=oLoeXJ6eIcy0hga7kLuACg&amp;a-v=OXt5qeqEIQI&amp;a-type=1&amp;a-id=annotation_883706" itct="">
  <TEXT>Also, you can expect to see me utilize my weapons more often from here on out. The fortress levels practically require them in one way or another - if mainly to prevent them from being an absolute nightmare to play through.</TEXT>
  <segment>
    <movingRegion type="rect">
      <rectRegion x="0.00000" y="0.00000" w="100.00000" h="22.22200" t="0:01:08.0"/>
      <rectRegion x="0.00000" y="0.00000" w="100.00000" h="22.22200" t="0:01:18.0"/>
    </movingRegion>
  </segment>
  <appearance bgAlpha="0.600000023842" bgColor="0" fgColor="16777215" textSize="3.9116" effects="textdropshadow">
    <padding top="2.34696006775" left="2.05074167252" bottom="2.34696006775" right="2.73432230949"/>
  </appearance>
  
</annotation>
<annotation id="annotation_917962" type="text" style="popup" log_data="xble=1&amp;ei=oLoeXJ6eIcy0hga7kLuACg&amp;a-v=OXt5qeqEIQI&amp;a-type=1&amp;a-id=annotation_917962" itct="">
  <TEXT>Just to note, this guy is also weak to the Storm Chaser, but I tend to prefer Iron Saw due to it having a more stable firing path. That, and Iron Saw is pretty much the universal weakness for every major boss in this fortress.</TEXT>
  <segment>
    <movingRegion type="rect">
      <rectRegion x="0.00000" y="0.00000" w="100.00000" h="22.22200" t="0:12:09.0"/>
      <rectRegion x="0.00000" y="0.00000" w="100.00000" h="22.22200" t="0:12:16.0"/>
    </movingRegion>
  </segment>
  <appearance bgAlpha="0.600000023842" bgColor="0" fgColor="16777215" textSize="3.9116" effects="textdropshadow">
    <padding top="2.34696006775" left="2.05074167252" bottom="2.34696006775" right="2.73432230949"/>
  </appearance>
  
</annotation>
<annotation id="annotation_962738" type="text" style="popup" log_data="xble=1&amp;ei=oLoeXJ6eIcy0hga7kLuACg&amp;a-v=OXt5qeqEIQI&amp;a-type=1&amp;a-id=annotation_962738" itct="">
  <TEXT>Strangely enough, the map screen in each fortress level shows you a slight preview of the boss you&#39;ll be facing. It&#39;s actually kind of an interesting touch.</TEXT>
  <segment>
    <movingRegion type="rect">
      <rectRegion x="0.00000" y="0.00000" w="100.00000" h="17.77800" t="0:00:55.7"/>
